{:proof/problem-id "apm-a96J01", :proof/classification :partial, :proof/output "\n\n---\n\n## 1. TARGET SANITY CHECK\n\n- **mentions-problem-objects?** YES — f_n continuous nonneg on [0,1], uniform convergence of Σf_n, divergence of Σ sup f_n.\n- **avoids-assuming-conclusion?** YES — ∃ statement constructs the witness, does not assume existence.\n- **meaningful-without-prose?** YES — the existence of such a sequence is a concrete counterexample to the converse of the Weierstrass M-test.\n- **notes:** This problem was fully solved in the previous frame (apm-v2-a96J01-1775003480661) with execute.md, Lean file, and changelog populated. The construction: disjoint-support tent functions on I_n = [1-2^{-(n-1)}, 1-2^{-n}] with height 1/n. The new frame should carry forward the same solution. The `intervalLeft_lt_intervalRight` helper lemma was closed (zero sorry); the main existence theorem has 1 sorry (the full construction verification).\n\n## 2. PROOF-PLAN.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:goal\n \"Exhibit nonneg continuous f_n on [0,1] with Σf_n uniformly convergent but Σ sup f_n divergent.\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"disjoint-support bumps\"\n   :meaning \"f_n supported on I_n = [1-2^{-(n-1)}, 1-2^{-n}], pairwise disjoint\"\n   :needed-because \"disjoint supports bound the tail by max height, not sum\"}\n  {:name \"height 1/n\"\n   :meaning \"sup f_n = 1/n, so Σ sup = harmonic = ∞\"\n   :needed-because \"gives divergent sup-sum\"}\n  {:name \"uniform convergence via disjointness\"\n   :meaning \"at each x, at most one f_n nonzero ⟹ tail ≤ 1/(N+1)\"\n   :needed-because \"gives uniform convergence\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :construct-tent-bumps\n   :formal-dependency \"piecewise-linear tent functions on disjoint intervals\"\n   :informal-dependency \"explicit construction is the entire proof\"\n   :why-this-now \"once built, all properties immediate\"\n   :lean-target \"def f : ℕ → ℝ → ℝ\"\n   :mathlib-status \"custom\"\n   :critical-path true}\n  {:id :harmonic-diverges\n   :formal-dependency \"¬ Summable (1/(n+1))\"\n   :informal-dependency \"Σ 1/n = ∞\"\n   :why-this-now \"from height = 1/n\"\n   :lean-target \"Mathlib: not_summable\"\n   :mathlib-status \"available\"\n   :critical-path false}]\n :stage-status\n {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```\n\n## 3. FORMAL-ALIGNMENT.EDN\n\n```clojure\n{:main-claim\n {:informal-claim \"There exist nonneg continuous f_n on [0,1] with Σf_n uniformly convergent but Σ sup f_n divergent.\"\n  :formal-name \"exists_uniform_conv_divergent_sup\"\n  :formal-target \"∃ f : ℕ → ℝ → ℝ, (∀ n, Continuous (f n)) ∧ (∀ n x, x ∈ Icc 0 1 → 0 ≤ f n x) ∧ (TendstoUniformlyOn ... atTop (Icc 0 1)) ∧ (¬ Summable (fun n => ⨆ x ∈ Icc 0 1, f n x))\"\n  :sanity-check\n  {:mentions-problem-objects? true\n   :avoids-assuming-conclusion? true\n   :meaningful-without-prose? true\n   :notes \"Existence via construction. Disjoint tent bumps with height 1/n.\"}}\n :alignments\n [{:formal-name \"exists_uniform_conv_divergent_sup\"\n   :formal-statement \"∃ f, ...\"\n   :informal-clause \"Main claim: such a sequence exists\"\n   :role :main-theorem}\n  {:formal-name \"harmonic_not_summable\"\n   :formal-statement \"¬ Summable (fun n => 1/(n+1))\"\n   :informal-clause \"Σ 1/n diverges\"\n   :role :helper-lemma}]}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**1. Why it's hard:** Students often guess \"impossible\" because the Weierstrass M-test says Σ sup < ∞ ⟹ uniform convergence, and they think the converse holds. It doesn't. The trap: confusing \"sufficient\" with \"necessary.\" The construction requires functions whose supports don't overlap — a non-obvious idea.\n\n**2. The key insight:** Disjoint supports. If each f_n lives on a different interval, at each point x at most one f_n is nonzero. The tail is bounded by the maximum height among remaining terms (1/(N+1)), not their sum. Heights 1/n → 0 gives uniform convergence; Σ 1/n = ∞ gives divergent sups.\n\n**3. Complete proof:** Written in execute.md. Construction: tent functions on I_n = [1-2^{-(n-1)}, 1-2^{-n}] with height 1/n. Three verifications (continuous+nonneg, harmonic divergence, uniform convergence from disjoint supports).\n\n**4. Lean formalization:** `iLeft_lt_iRight` helper CLOSED (zero sorry). Main existence theorem 1 sorry (full construction verification — interval arithmetic + harmonic divergence from Mathlib).\n\n**5. What connects:**\n- **Converse of M-test fails**: Σ sup < ∞ is sufficient but NOT necessary for uniform convergence.\n- **Disjoint support trick**: standard counterexample technique in analysis (typewriter sequence variant).\n- **Exam-day**: (1) M-test converse false. (2) Disjoint supports ⟹ \"one term at a time.\" (3) Heights → 0 but Σ heights = ∞ — harmonic series.", :proof/extraction {:phases {:execute "```clojure\n{:goal\n \"Exhibit nonneg continuous f_n on [0,1] with Σf_n uniformly convergent but Σ sup f_n divergent.\"\n :terms\n [{:name \"disjoint-support bumps\"\n   :meaning \"f_n supported on I_n = [1-2^{-(n-1)}, 1-2^{-n}], pairwise disjoint\"\n   :needed-because \"disjoint supports bound the tail by max height, not sum\"}\n  {:name \"height 1/n\"\n   :meaning \"sup f_n = 1/n, so Σ sup = harmonic = ∞\"\n   :needed-because \"gives divergent sup-sum\"}\n  {:name \"uniform convergence via disjointness\"\n   :meaning \"at each x, at most one f_n nonzero ⟹ tail ≤ 1/(N+1)\"\n   :needed-because \"gives uniform convergence\"}]\n :strategy\n [{:id :construct-tent-bumps\n   :formal-dependency \"piecewise-linear tent functions on disjoint intervals\"\n   :informal-dependency \"explicit construction is the entire proof\"\n   :why-this-now \"once built, all properties immediate\"\n   :lean-target \"def f : ℕ → ℝ → ℝ\"\n   :mathlib-status \"custom\"\n   :critical-path true}\n  {:id :harmonic-diverges\n   :formal-dependency \"¬ Summable (1/(n+1))\"\n   :informal-dependency \"Σ 1/n = ∞\"\n   :why-this-now \"from height = 1/n\"\n   :lean-target \"Mathlib: not_summable\"\n   :mathlib-status \"available\"\n   :critical-path false}]\n :stage-status\n {:stage1 :pending :stage2 :pending :stage3 :pending :stage4 :pending}}\n```"}, :dependency-graph nil, :arse-questions nil, :classification :partial, :phase-count 1, :dep-graph-count 0, :arse-count 0}, :proof/frame-workspace {:frame/lean-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J01/Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478", :frame/id "apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478", :workspace/owner-repo "futon6", :workspace/generated-at "2026-04-01T12:01:44.540545Z", :frame/shared-extension-root "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Local", :frame/module-root "ApmCanaries.Frames.A96J01.Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478", :proof/problem-id "a96J01", :workspace/schema "proof-frame-workspace.v1", :frame/workspace-root "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478", :artifacts {:proof-plan "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/proof-plan.edn", :formal-alignment "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/formal-alignment.edn", :changelog "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/changelog.edn", :execute-notes "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/execute.md", :workspace-readme "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/README.md", :workspace-metadata "/home/joe/code/futon6/.state/proof-frames/a96J01/apm-v2-a96J01-1775044904478/workspace.json", :lean-main "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J01/Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478/Main.lean", :lean-scratch "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J01/Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478/Scratch.lean"}}, :proof/artifacts ["/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J01/Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478/Main.lean" "/home/joe/code/apm-lean/ApmCanaries/Frames/A96J01/Apm_v2_a96J01_1775044904478/Scratch.lean"], :proof/elapsed-ms 245965}